# TOOLS.md — Developer

## My folder

- **Ticket folder:** `workspace/agents/developers/{{ kanban_slot }}/`
- **No ticket file in this folder** → no op.
- **One ticket file** (e.g. `wawa.proj.default.implementation.fix-login-bug.md`) → work on it until done, then move it as below.

## Project and source discovery

- **Projects root:** `{{ host_projects_root_hint }}/` (e.g. `workspace/projects/`)
- **Project location pointer:** `{{ host_projects_root_hint }}`/`{project_id}`/.project.location — single line, absolute path or canonical URI of the source repository
- **Project metadata:** `{{ host_projects_root_hint }}`/`{project_id}`/project.md — shared knowledge for developers
- **project_id inference:** from ticket filename, first dot-separated segment before the mode token (`implementation` | `design` | `websearch` | `codesearch`)
  - Example: `wawa.proj.default.implementation.fix-login-bug.md` → project_id is `wawa.proj.default`

## Worktree conventions

- **Worktree naming:** `wt-{ticket_id}` (e.g. `wt-TICKET-001`) or `wt-{ticket_slug}` (from filename/frontmatter)
- **Branch naming:** derived from ticket intent — use the ticket's goal, not your name, so others can take over
- **Location:** inside the repo's worktree directory (project convention)

## Ticket file naming pattern

- Format: `{project_id}.{mode}.{slug}.md` or `{project_id}.{mode}.{slug}.md.lock`
- Modes: `implementation` | `design` | `websearch` | `codesearch`
- Example: `wawa.proj.default.implementation.fix-login-bug.md`

## When the ticket is done

Move the ticket file to the **same project's** `waiting_for_verification/` folder:

- **Path:** `workspace/projects/{project_id}/waiting_for_verification/`
- **project_id** comes from the ticket filename: first part before the first dot-separated mode token.
  Example: `wawa.proj.default.implementation.fix-login-bug.md` → project_id is `wawa.proj.default` → move to `workspace/projects/wawa.proj.default/waiting_for_verification/`.

Keep the filename unchanged when moving. Do not move until tests pass and you have appended the implementation summary to the ticket file.
